{"id":14881058,"mediaExerciseId":"b2b53620-aa5d-45d2-85a5-1c3635d64065","exerciseName":"9","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612313,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":233,"solutions":[{"id":6003234,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, **we have to determine the price of the bond that pays no coupons, but we should calculate it on the semiannual level.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"A zero-coupon bond does not provide coupons from the issuing until maturity. But the holder and the issuer should calculate interest according to the tax on the annual level, although there are no payouts. The debt is paid back on the date of maturity, and the offered price is significantly lower than the actual value.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/8910d180ad8dce337dca0296edf70b99/241d7ac88e1fcdd8fac59b3b42d28f6a/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/8910d180ad8dce337dca0296edf70b99/241d7ac88e1fcdd8fac59b3b42d28f6a/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"We have all the necessary information to fill the formula, we just have to be careful because, in the exercise, we have a requirement to consider semiannual periods.\n\n$$\\text{price}=\\dfrac{\\text{FV}}{\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)^\\text{n}}$$\n\nFV-face value\n\nYTM- yield to maturity\n\nn-periods\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":173,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/8910d180ad8dce337dca0296edf70b99/74f5000df6a401a1c2388f930f00df21/lateximg_large.png","width":1004},"regular":{"height":88,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/8910d180ad8dce337dca0296edf70b99/74f5000df6a401a1c2388f930f00df21/lateximg.png","width":502}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"We just need to divide the YTM by two because we will get paid twice per year. But the period we should multiply by 2. \n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\n\\text{YTM}&=\\dfrac{4.2\\%}{2}\\\\[15pt]\n&=2.1\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The YTM is 2.1\\%.**\n\n\n\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":330,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/8910d180ad8dce337dca0296edf70b99/d804f2b8f5d968ed460176b148fc9d7a/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":167,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/8910d180ad8dce337dca0296edf70b99/d804f2b8f5d968ed460176b148fc9d7a/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, we calculate the number of periods. \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{n}&=17\\times2\\\\[15pt]\n&=34\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**We should consider 34 periods**.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's calculate the price of the bond.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{price}&=\\dfrac{\\$10,000}{\\left(1+2.1\\%\\right)^{34}}\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\boxed{\\$4,933.15}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The price of the bond is \\$4,933.15.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":288,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/8910d180ad8dce337dca0296edf70b99/59154689416511c1787f5a9e32fc9ea2/lateximg_large.png","width":633},"regular":{"height":145,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/8910d180ad8dce337dca0296edf70b99/59154689416511c1787f5a9e32fc9ea2/lateximg.png","width":317}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"f0ca0259-d4fa-4e0a-a0a4-d926d6e1eb11","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881059,"exerciseName":"10","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"77206062-9a79-45d8-ba0a-c7ee62255096","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-10-77206062-9a79-45d8-ba0a-c7ee62255096"},{"id":14881060,"exerciseName":"11","page":234,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"983136f3-2679-44a5-ae28-cccd340ce68c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-11-983136f3-2679-44a5-ae28-cccd340ce68c"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881057,"exerciseName":"8","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"fa5b21dc-f94d-4ae8-9644-143e78afefa7","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-8-fa5b21dc-f94d-4ae8-9644-143e78afefa7"},{"id":14881056,"exerciseName":"7","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"2e053a52-210d-4a10-8229-2a699d541d43","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-o